The article summarizes a White House press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney. The briefing covered various topics including the Olympics, gun control, Syria, and tax cuts. Carney discussed the President's position on gun control, stating that he supports common-sense measures to keep guns out of the hands of those who should not have them. He also mentioned the President's support for the reinstatement of the assault weapons ban. Carney emphasized the need for a comprehensive approach to addressing violence in the country, including education and economic opportunities. On the topic of tax cuts, Carney argued that the President supports extending tax cuts for 98% of Americans, but not for the top 2% of income earners. He criticized House Republicans for holding hostage the middle-class tax cuts. Carney also addressed questions about the national security leaks, Olympic security, and the President's White House Initiative for Educational Excellence for African Americans.